21/08/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- An army officer was seriously injured during new clashes between the Turkish security forces and the terrorist organisation Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) on Sunday (20 August).
Local authorities say fighting erupted when an army patrol came across PKK militants in the mountainous southeast region of Nusaybin in the Mardin province.
In other news, Sirnak province authorities reported on Friday that a 70-year old man died in a landmine incident in the Gorumlu district the previous evening.
The man stepped on the mine, believed to have been planted by the PKK.
(Zaman, Cihan - 20/08/06;
NTV - 18/08/06)
